post_survey.music_making: Sing solo and in choir settings my whole life. Played violin for a year.
post_survey.activities: Doing chores, working out, playing games
post_survey.habits: Most of my music listening is done when I'm working out. I rarely listen to music when I play games since I like to enjoy the original score as well. When I discover a song or album I really like, I'll have it on repeat for up to a month.
post_survey.habit_change: I rarely listened to music intentionally. I usually listened to the radio, but otherwise, listening to music was not an activity in itself for me. However, once I started tracking my music listening, I realized that I enjoyed seeking out new artists and genres to listen to.
